                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 383.516/56.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Blanchard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-26T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1915—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 23. Say to the Government that this Government can not consent to
                    the removal of funds belonging to the Bank without which it is impossible for
                    Bank to live up to its contractual obligations. Advise the Government that any
                    attempt to remove the Bank’s funds will compel you to consider means of
                    preventing such violation of the rights of foreign stockholders.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
